Let \(X\) and \(Y\) be random variables with the joint probability density function given by:
\[
f_{X,Y}(x,y) = \begin{cases} 
0.25ye^{-y} & \text{if } 0 \leq |x| \leq y \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\]
Find the conditional density \(f_{X|Y = y}(x)\) and identify the conditional distribution \(X|_{Y = y}\). Then, use the law of total expectation to find \(E[X^2]\).
